    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A MemoryError with Pandas and CSVs is often because list comprehensions load *everything* into memory at once.  Generators, on the other hand, yield results one at a time—like a tiny, lazy stream of data. This means instead of holding all the processed rows in RAM, your script only holds the current row in memory. For huge datasets, this difference between storing a whole pile versus just handing out one item at a time is the difference between success and a memory crash.",
